<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-02-04T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-02-04T15:00:00-05:00" n="1241" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1241">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">125.0093/2–449: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Chargé in the Philippines</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Lockett</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-02-04T15:00:00-05:00">February
                                    4, 1949—3 p. m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>146. Emb Manila instructed pick up passports any evacuées who intend
                            return China contravention Depts instructions Deptel 128, Jan 28, Deptel
                            157 Feb 2 to Nanking, Deptel 116 Jan 31 to Manila.</p>
                        <p>Dept will entertain special requests for return certain dependents
                            unusual circumstances only after careful consideration and Emb Nanking
                            recommendations.</p>
                        <p>Sent Manila. Repeated Nanking [171,] Canton [31,] telCan [7,] Shanghai
                            [190].</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>